  "text": "Thus, an alternative method is proposed which is Stimulated Brillouin Scattering (SBS) to overcome above mention problem. Stimulated Brillouin Scattering (SBS) has generally been perceived as one of the causes degrading framework execution in fiber optic systems because of the impact that the signal energy is exchanged to the back scattering signal and SBS has low threshold. In any case, SBS has advantages qualities, for example, frequency selective amplification that can be boost up to microwave and mm-waves photonics applications [CITATION_1] .",
